# Dev-1 Contribution

## Project Structure & Configuration

### Core Configuration
1. `.env` - Environment variables
2. `app/Config/config.php` - Loads .env, defines constants
3. `app/Config/database.php` - PDO connection via `getDB()`
4. `app/Config/constants.php` - Roles, statuses, HTTP codes

### Security Components
5. `app/Security/AES.php` - AES-256-CBC encrypt/decrypt (random IV, stored with cipher)
6. `app/Security/JWT.php` - Generates and validates access tokens
7. `app/Security/CSRF.php` - Generates and validates CSRF via session using `getallheaders()`
8. `app/Security/Hash.php` - bcrypt password hash and verify

### Middleware
9. `app/Middleware/AuthMiddleware.php` - Reads Bearer token from Authorization header, returns payload
10. `app/Middleware/CsrfMiddleware.php` - Validates X-CSRF-Token header, skips auth routes

### Helpers
11. `app/Helpers/Response.php` - Plain JSON response (AES on response disabled for now)
12. `app/Helpers/Validator.php` - Required, email, min, in validation

### Routing & Controllers
13. `app/Routes/api.php` - Route function maps METHOD + URI to controller
14. `app/Controllers/AuthController.php` - Register, login, refresh, csrfToken

### Services
15. `app/Services/AuthService.php` - Register, login, refresh, logout logic

### Entry Point
16. `public/index.php` - Entry point, loads CSRF middleware, loads routes
17. `public/.htaccess` - Rewrites all requests to index.php

---

## Authentication Flow

### Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/csrf-token` | Returns CSRF token, stored in PHP session |
| POST | `/register` | Accepts raw JSON (AES disabled for now), creates user |
| POST | `/login` | Returns `access_token` in response body, sets `refresh_token` in HttpOnly cookie |
| POST | `/refresh-token` | Reads refresh token from cookie, returns new access token |

### Token Management

* **Access Token** → Sent by client in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
* **Refresh Token** → Stored in `users` table columns (`refresh_token`, `refresh_token_expires_at`)
* **No separate refresh_tokens table** - Tokens stored directly on users table


STAFF & PRESCRIPTION API UPDATE
================================

NEW FILES
---------
app/Controllers/StaffController.php
app/Controllers/PrescriptionController.php
app/Services/StaffService.php
app/Services/PrescriptionService.php
app/Routes/api.php  (updated)


STAFF ENDPOINTS
---------------
GET    /staff               - list all staff
GET    /staff/:id           - get one
POST   /staff               - create  { "user_id":2, "specialization":"Cardiology", "status":"active" }
PUT    /staff/:id           - update  { "specialization":"Neurology", "status":"inactive" }
DELETE /staff/:id           - delete


PRESCRIPTION ENDPOINTS
----------------------
GET    /prescriptions                      - list all
GET    /prescriptions/:id                  - get one
GET    /patients/:id/prescriptions         - by patient
GET    /appointments/:id/prescription      - by appointment
POST   /prescriptions                      - create  { "patient_id":1, "appointment_id":1, "medicines":"..." }
PUT    /prescriptions/:id                  - update  { "medicines":"..." }
PATCH  /prescriptions/:id/status           - { "status":"verified" }
DELETE /prescriptions/:id                  - delete

STATUS FLOW: created → verified → dispensed


ENCRYPTION
----------
medicines field in prescriptions table is AES encrypted on save, decrypted on read.
AES_KEY must be set in .env


HEADERS (all requests)
----------------------
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
X-CSRF-Token:  <csrf_token>
Content-Type:  application/json


ROLE PERMISSIONS
----------------
Staff   create/update/delete  → admin only
Staff   read                  → admin, doctor, nurse
Prescription create           → doctor only
Prescription status update    → admin, doctor, pharmacist
Prescription read             → admin, doctor, pharmacist, nurse